topic.title: System Information Region

body.p: This region is used to store the board system information. All fields are read only. Writes to this region are ignored.

body.p: Partition ID of the currently running BL2 partition. It should be 0x01(BL2 partition 0) or 0x02(BL2 partition 1);

body.p: Partition ID of configuration partition currently used. It should be 0x05(Configuration partition 0) or 0x06(Configuration partition 1);

p.b: Partition ID of the currently running firmware partition (0x2050)

body.p: Partition ID of running firmware partition. It should be 0x07(Main Firmware image partition 0) or 0x08(Main Firmware image partition 1);
the chip/silicon ID for the Switchtec device.
the build type for the Switchtec device.
0x00: Unknown

0xFF: Invalid.

p.b: This section (0x2100 - 0x2200) is to store device identification information, which are all in big endian. The values are affected by enable vendor settings(0x2100) and Enable seeprom(0x2101). There are two cases:
case 1. P2P related information(0x2110 - 0x2127) and mac address(0x2128- 0x212f)

table.title: source data case 1 of device identification

entry.p: Most fields are read from configure file. But "P2P Device ID" and "Subsystem ID" have a special case:
1. When "P2P Vendor ID" = 0x11F8, "P2P Device ID" is set as Firmware Device ID, which is just the same as gas register@0x2000.
2. When "Subsystem Vendor ID" = 0x11F8, "Subsystem ID" is set as Firmware Device ID, which is just the same as gas register@0x2000.
Otherwise, the registers are read from configure file.
If seeprom fru data is accessible and valid, the data source is from Seeprom. Otherwise the data source is the same as the rule of (enable_seeprom = 0), details see the above.

p.b: case 2. Other registers in this section.

table.title: source data case 2 of device identification

entry.p: If seeprom fru data is accessible and valid, the data source is from Seeprom, otherwise from configure file.

body.p: Bit 0 - Refer to Enable Vendor Settings.
All other bits reserved.
Bit 0 - Refer to the field named "Enable Seeprom'' from configure file Enable SEEPROM.
Bit 7 - Seeprom data is valid or not.
Only when bit0 is 1, bit7 is needed to be checked. That is, Enable Seeprom@gas 0x2101 = b10000001, seeprom fru data is valid; otherwise, seeprom fru data isn't used by Switchtec FW.
Bits 7:0 - Seeprom TWI address in the configuration file
Refer to SEEPROM TWI Address.
Bits 11:8 - Seeprom TWI bus id Refer to SEERPOM TWI Bus ID.
Bit 12 - Refer to SEEPROM TWI Offset Width.
Bits 15:13 - Reserved.
